<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd" []>
<task xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" id="specifying-font-of-tags" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:oasis:names:tc:dita:xsd:task.xsd:1.1">
  <title>Specifying Font of Tags</title>
  <taskbody id="body">
    <context>
      <p>When you switch to the Markup Mode, markup tags are displayed. You can change  font metrics of  tag names: the  font  family, font style, size, effects and script.</p>
    </context>
    <steps>
      <step>
        <cmd>Call up the <keyword>Preferences Dialog</keyword>.</cmd>
        <info>
          <p>To call up the <keyword>Preferences Dialog</keyword>, choose <menucascade>
              <uicontrol>Tools</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>Preferences</uicontrol>
            </menucascade>.</p>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Select the <keyword>Tag Style tab</keyword>.</cmd>
        <info>
          <fig>
            <title>Tag Style tab.</title>
            <image href="preferences-dialog-tag-style-tab-tag-font.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          </fig>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>To change font metrics of tag names, do the following:</cmd>
        <substeps>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Choose font</uicontrol> button next to the <uicontrol>Tag font</uicontrol> field.</cmd>
          </substep>
          <substep>
            <cmd>In the <keyword>Select Font Dialog</keyword>, specify the font and click <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info>
              <fig>
                <title>Select Font Dialog.</title>
                <image href="select-font-dialog.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
              </fig>
            </info>
          </substep>
        </substeps>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Apply</uicontrol> button to apply the settings.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Close</uicontrol> button to close the dialog.</cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
</task>
